Description: Prince Vald is forever cursed to transform into a demon every night, unless a powerful sorcerer named Halvi can help him break the spell!
Title: CRIMSON SPELL, VOL. 5
Author: Ayano Yamane

Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and helps usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume, the truth behind Ichigo’s soul-cutter sword is revealed.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 61
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: A middle-school student is framed for the murder of his classmates and then sentenced to a prison that doubles as a demented theme park in this new series.
Title: DEADMAN WONDERLAND, VOL. 4
Author: Jinsei Katoka and Kazuma Kondou
Contributor: by Jinsei Katoka and Kazuma Kondou

Description: The Fairy Tail, a group of powerful wizards, encounter a town where everything is frozen, including giants and the Eternal Flame.
Title: FAIRY TAIL, VOL. 41
Author: Hiro Mashima

Description: Ritsuka is heartbroken over his brother’s death, but will the insight that Soubi, a mysterious, handsome college student, has make things any better?
Title: LOVELESS, VOL. 12
Author: Yun Kouga

Description: Soma Yukihira enrolls in a prestigious culinary academy to hone his cooking skills, but can he succeed in a highly competitive school that has only a 10 percent graduation rate?
Title: FOOD WARS!, VOL. 1
Author: Yuto Tsukudo and Shun Saeki
Contributor: by Yuto Tsukudo and Shun Saeki

Description: The origins of the Survey Corps leaders Levi and Erwin are told in this spin–off series.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: NO REGRETS, VOL. 1
Author: Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama
Contributor: by Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama

Description: Life in a high school filled with werewolves and vampires continues.
Title: ROSARIO+VAMPIRE, SEASON II, VOL. 13
Author: Akihisa Ikeda

Description: Ash Blake attends the Ansarivan Dragonar Academy, where each student rides their own dragon. But Ash’s dragon, Eco, is different and can transform into a human girl.
Title: DRAGONAR ACADEMY, VOL. 3
Author: Shiki Mizuchi and Ran

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama
